ony Corporation]] \u2013 ([[Fenton, Missouri]])\n* Test Drive Technologies ([[St. Louis]])\n* [[TricorBraun]] \u2013 ([[Creve Coeur, Missouri]])\n* True Manufacturing Company \u2013 ([[O'Fallon, Missouri]]) \n* [[Vi-Jon Laboratories]]  \u2013 ([[Overland, Missouri]])\n* [[Wells Fargo Advisors]] \u2013 ([[St. Louis]]) [formerly [[Wachovia Securities]] and prior to that [[A.G. Edwards]]]\n* [[Wood River Refinery]]  \u2013 ([[Roxana, Illinois]])\n* [[World Wide Technology]]  \u2013 ([[Maryland Heights, Missouri]])\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Sports==\n{{expand section|date=August 2018}}\n\nThe Greater St. Louis area is currently home to two professional sports teams: the [[St. Louis Blues]] ([[National Hockey League|NHL]]) who won the Stanley Cup in 2019, and the [[St. Louis Cardinals]] ([[Major League Baseball|MLB]]), who have won 19 National League Pennants, and 11 World Series Championshis.<ref>{{cite web |title=Greatest sports events in St. Louis |url=https://www.stltoday.com/sports/greatest-sports-events-in-st-louis/collection_b554f77f-fb35-5a3c-bf0c-ba2cc99237bc.html#1 |website=STLtoday.com |publisher=St. Louis Post Dispatch |accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[St. Louis cuisine]]\n* [[List of high schools in Greater St. Louis]]\n* [[List of colleges and universities in Greater St. Louis]]\n* [[Missouri census statistical areas]]\n* {{Portal-inline|United States}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}} <!--added above External links/Sources by script-assisted edit-->\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.ewgateway.org/ East-West Gateway Council of Governments]\n* [http://www.slcec.com/ St. Louis County Economic Council]\n\n{{St. Louis MSA}}\n{{Metro-East}}\n{{Missouri}}\n{{Illinois}}\n{{USLargestMetros}}\n\n{{coord missing|Missouri}}\n\n[[Category:Greater St. Louis| ]]\n[[Category:Metropolitan areas of Missouri|Saint Louis]]\n[[Category:Metropolitan areas of Illinois|Saint Louis]]\n[[Category:Regions of Missouri|Saint Louis]]\n[[Category:Regions of Illinois|Saint Louis]]\n", "name_user": "Jellysandwich0", "label": "safe", "comment": "It became a regional headquarters for Federated and was soon closed.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Greater_St._Louis"}
