: Shattered Blade|publisher=[[IGN]]|accessdate=May 27, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"AUBladeRelease\">{{cite web|url=http://au.ign.com/games/bleach-shattered-blade/wii-833630|title=Bleach: Shattered Blade|publisher=[[IGN]]|accessdate=May 29, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"EUBladeRelease\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nintendo.co.uk/Games/Wii/Bleach-Shattered-Blade-280660.html|title=Bleach: Shattered Blade|publisher=[[Nintendo]]|accessdate=May 29, 2014}}</ref>\n|release=2006\u2014[[Wii]]<ref name=\"JPBladeRelease\"/>\n|notes=* Released in Japan as {{Nihongo|''Bleach Wii Hakujin Kirameku Rondo''|Bleach Wii\u3000\u767d\u5203\u304d\u3089\u3081\u304f\u8f2a\u821e\u66f2||Bleach: Shattered Blade}}<ref name=\"JPBladeRelease\"/>\n* Features a 2-player battle mode<ref name=\"JPBladeRelease\"/>\n}}\n{{Video game titles/item\n|title=Bleach: Versus Crusade\n|date={{vgrelease|JP|December 18, 2008}}\n|refs=<ref name=\"JPVCRelease\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/wii/software/rbxj/|title=Bleach \u30d0\u30fc\u30b5\u30b9\u30fb\u30af\u30eb\u30bb\u30a4\u30c9|publisher=[[Nintendo]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=May 29, 2014}}</ref>\n|release=2008\u2014Wii<ref name=\"JPVCRelease\"/>\n|notes=* Released in Japan as {{Nihongo|''Bleach B\u0101sasu Kuruseido''|Bleach \u30d0\u30fc\u30b5\u30b9\u30fb\u30af\u30eb\u30bb\u30a4\u30c9||Bleach: Versus Crusade}}<ref name=\"JPVCRelease\"/>\n* Visitors to the official website were allowed to vote for which two characters they wanted on the cover of the game; the winning pair was [[Ichigo Kurosaki]] and [[Rukia Kuchiki]]<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090318143112/http://bleach.sega.jp/vs/package.html|archivedate=March 18, 2009|url=http://bleach.sega.jp/vs/package.html|title=Bleach Vs Package contest|publisher=[[Sega]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=May 31, 2014}}</ref>\n* Features multiplayer systems<ref name=\"JPVCRelease\"/><ref name=\"Nintendo Wi-Fi\" group=\"n\"/>\n}}\n}}\n\n===''Bleach: Heat the Soul''===\n{{Main|Bleach: Heat the Soul (series)}}\nThe {{Nihongo|''Bleach: Heat the Soul''|Bleach: \u30d2\u30fc\u30c8\u30fb\u30b6\u30fb\u30bd\u30a6\u30eb}} series is a series of [[fighting game]]s developed by [[Eighting]] and published by [[SCEI]].\n{{Video game titles|\n{{Video game titles/item\n|title=Bleach: Heat the Soul\n|date={{vgrelease|JP|March 24, 2005}}\n|refs=<ref name=\"HTSRelease\">{{cite web|url=http://www.jp.playstation.com/software/title/ucjs10008.html|title=Bleach \u301c\u30d2\u30fc\u30c8\u30fb\u30b6\u30fb\u30bd\u30a6\u30eb\u301c|publisher=[[PlayStation]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=May 29, 2014}}</ref>\n|release=2005\u2014[[PlayStation Portable]]<ref name=\"HTSRelease\"/>\n|notes=* Features a versus mode between players<ref name=\"HTSRelease\"/><ref name=\"Heat the Soul Online service\" group=\"n\">Online functionality via ''PlayStation Network'' was available but it has been terminated.</ref>\n* Released under ''[[The Best (PlayStation range)|The Best]]'' label on March 2, 2006 in Japan<ref name=\"HTSRR\">{{cite web|url=http://www.jp.playstation.com/software/title/ucjs18005.html|title=Bleach \u301c\u30d2\u30fc\u30c8\u30fb\u30b6\u30fb\u30bd\u30a6\u30eb\u301c PSP\u00ae the Best|publisher=[[PlayStation]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=May 29, 2014}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Video game titles/item\n|title=Bleach: Heat the Soul 2\n|date={{vgrelease|JP|September 1, 2005}}\n|refs=<ref name=\"HTS2Release\">{{cite web|url=http://www.jp.playstation.com/software/title/ucjs10017.html|title=Bleach \u301c\u30d2\u30fc\u30c8\u30fb\u30b6\u30fb\u30bd\u30a6\u30eb2\u301c |publisher=[[PlayStation]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=May 29, 2014}}</ref>\n|release=2005\u2014PlayStation Portable<ref name=\"HTS2Release\"/>\n|notes=* Features a versus mode between players<ref name=\"HTS2Release\"/><ref name=\"Heat the Soul Online service\" group=\"n\"/>\n* Released under ''The Best'' label on November 30, 2006 in Japan<ref name=\"HTS2RR\">{{cite web|url=http://www.jp.playstation.com/software/title/ucjs18010.html|title=Bleach