gs-platforming-slashing/|title=''Bleach DS 4th: Flame Bringer'' brings platforming, slashing|author=JC Fletcher|publisher=Joystiq (Nintendo)|date=May 19, 2009|accessdate=May 29, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140529123742/http://www.joystiq.com/2009/05/19/bleach-ds-4th-flame-bringer-brings-platforming-slashing/|archive-date=May 29, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* Released in Japan as {{Nihongo|''Bleach DS 4th Fureimu Buring\u0101''|Bleach DS 4th\uff1a\u30d5\u30ec\u30a4\u30e0\u30fb\u30d6\u30ea\u30f3\u30ac\u30fc||Bleach DS 4th: Flame Bringer}}<ref name=\"JPFlameRelease\"/>\n}}\n}}\n\n===Bleach Nintendo Home Consoles===\n\nThe ''Bleach Nintendo Home Console'' series is a series of [[fighting game]]s published by [[Sega]], with the first two being developed by [[Polygon Magic]] and ''Versus Crusade'' being developed by [[Treasure (company)|Treasure Co. Ltd]].\n{{Video game titles|\n{{Video game titles/item\n|title=Bleach GC: Tasogare ni Mamieru Shinigami\n|date={{vgrelease|JP|December 8, 2005}}\n|refs=<ref name=\"JPGCRelease\">{{cite web|url=http://sega.jp/gc/bleach/|title=Bleach GC \u9ec4\u660f\u306b\u307e\u307f\u3048\u308b\u6b7b\u795e|publisher=[[Sega]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=May 29, 2014}}</ref>\n|release=2005\u2014[[GameCube|Nintendo GameCube]]<ref name=\"JPGCRelease\"/>\n|notes=* Released in Japan as {{Nihongo|''Bleach GC Tasogare ni Mamieru Shinigami''|Bleach GC \u9ec4\u660f\u306b\u307e\u307f\u3048\u308b\u6b7b\u795e||Bleach GC: Death Gods Meeting in the Twilight}}<ref name=\"JPGCRelease\"/>\n* Includes a 2-player battle mode<ref name=\"JPGCRelease\"/>\n}}\n{{Video game titles/item\n|title=Bleach: Shattered Blade\n|date={{vgrelease|JP|December 14, 2006}}{{vgrelease|NA|October 9, 2007}}{{vgrelease|AUS|February 28, 2008}}{{vgrelease|EU|February 29, 2008}}\n|refs=<ref name=\"JPBladeRelease\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/wii/software/rblj/|title=Bleach Wii\u3000\u767d\u5203\u304d\u3089\u3081\u304f\u8f2a\u821e\u66f2|publisher=[[Nintendo]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=May 29, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"USBladeRelease\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/games/bleach-shattered-blade/wii-833630|title=Bleach: Shattered Blade|publisher=[[IGN]]|accessdate=May 27, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"AUBladeRelease\">{{cite web|url=http://au.ign.com/games/bleach-shattered-blade/wii-833630|title=Bleach: Shattered Blade|publisher=[[IGN]]|accessdate=May 29, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"EUBladeRelease\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nintendo.co.uk/Games/Wii/Bleach-Shattered-Blade-280660.html|title=Bleach: Shattered Blade|publisher=[[Nintendo]]|accessdate=May 29, 2014}}</ref>\n|release=2006\u2014[[Wii]]<ref name=\"JPBladeRelease\"/>\n|notes=* Released in Japan as {{Nihongo|''Bleach Wii Hakujin Kirameku Rondo''|Bleach Wii\u3000\u767d\u5203\u304d\u3089\u3081\u304f\u8f2a\u821e\u66f2||Bleach: Shattered Blade}}<ref name=\"JPBladeRelease\"/>\n* Features a 2-player battle mode<ref name=\"JPBladeRelease\"/>\n}}\n{{Video game titles/item\n|title=Bleach: Versus Crusade\n|date={{vgrelease|JP|December 18, 2008}}\n|refs=<ref name=\"JPVCRelease\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/wii/software/rbxj/|title=Bleach \u30d0\u30fc\u30b5\u30b9\u30fb\u30af\u30eb\u30bb\u30a4\u30c9|publisher=[[Nintendo]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=May 29, 2014}}</ref>\n|release=2008\u2014Wii<ref name=\"JPVCRelease\"/>\n|notes=* Released in Japan as {{Nihongo|''Bleach B\u0101sasu Kuruseido''|Bleach \u30d0\u30fc\u30b5\u30b9\u30fb\u30af\u30eb\u30bb\u30a4\u30c9||Bleach: Versus Crusade}}<ref name=\"JPVCRelease\"/>\n* Visitors to the official website were allowed to vote for which two characters they wanted on the cover of the game; the winning pair was [[Ichigo Kurosaki]] and [[Rukia Kuchiki]]<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090318143112/http://bleach.sega.jp/vs/package.html|archivedate=March 18, 2009|url=http://bleach.sega.jp/vs/package.html|title=Bleach Vs Package contest|publisher=[[Sega]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=May 31, 2014}}</ref>\n* 